	<doc for="SingleConverter">
		<summary>
			<para> Provides a type
      converter to convert single-precision, floating point number objects to and from various other
      representations.</para>
		</summary>
		<remarks>
			<para>This converter can only convert a single-precision,
      floating point number object to and from a string. The <see cref="System.Single"/> value type
      represents a single-precision 32-bit number with values ranging
      from negative 3.402823e38 to positive 3.402823e38.</para>
			<note type="note">
      You should never create an instance
      of <see cref="System.ComponentModel.SingleConverter"/>. Instead, call the <see cref="System.ComponentModel.TypeDescriptor.GetConverter"/> method of <see cref="System.ComponentModel.TypeDescriptor"/>. For more information, see the examples
      in the <see cref="System.ComponentModel.TypeConverter"/> base class and
   <see topic="cpconImplementingTypeConverter"/>.
   </note>
		</remarks>
		<example>
			<para> The following sample converts a variable of type
   <see cref="System.Single"/>
   
   to a string, and vice versa.</para>
			<codelink SampleID="Converters" SnippetID="19"/>
		</example>
	</doc></docs>
